# 💡 Founder Recommendation

As a solo founder, I recommend following the **"1-1-1 Rule"** for the first six months after launch.

### Every Day (15–20 minutes)

* Check if the app is online.
* Review failed uploads.
* Look for new support emails.

### Every Week (1–2 hours)

* Fix the highest-priority bug.
* Review user feedback.
* Test one important workflow (upload → OCR → AI → history).

### Every Month

* Release one update.
* Review cloud costs.
* Plan the next month's priorities.

This routine is manageable for one person and helps you steadily improve the product without becoming overwhelmed.

